That is: if your module is free, you can always write `Q = B.toQuadraticMap`, which means that the base change exists.

This doesn't go as far as changing `QuadraticForm.baseChange`, as this would trade one generality (`Invertible (2 : R)`) for another (`Module.Free R M`).

Yes, I find the fact that it keeps saying when it first posted, rather than when it was last edited, confusing.  Maybe there is a way of changing that?

I think it's a feature, so long as the comment is early enough in the list of comments. This fails to be the case only if:
* The PR predates the introduction of the PR summary bot
* The author has made a lot of commits before opening the PR

both of which should be pretty rare. So I think it's fine as it is!
